  <div class="content">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="small-12 columns">
        <div class="field body"><p>At Aerosim, we realize it takes a team of dedicated employees with a variety of skills to create a truly great company. Thanks to the team we’ve developed over the years, Aerosim is considered by our most important critics – our customers – to be an innovative company backed by excellent products with reliable and effective customer support. As a growing company, Aerosim offers a world of opportunity for those who are ready to excel. If you are excited about aviation, simulation and a challenge to innovate, Aerosim may be the place for you. Check back often for a current list of our permanent, contract and internship opportunities. </p>
<h4><br /><br />
Current Job Openings - Aerosim Technologies<br /><br />
 </h4>
<h3>AVIATION COURSEWARE DEVELOPER</h3>
<p><strong>Job Description </strong></p>
<p>Aerosim Technologies is planning for tomorrow. Our team of dedicated individuals are turning imaginative ideas into leading products and services that provide elegant solutions for some of the toughest challenges in aviation training. Aerosim is seeking qualified, energetic, self-starting Aviation Courseware Developer to build engaging training content for the civil and military aviation markets. The Aviation Courseware Developer will be designing, developing, building and testing interactive content for aircraft systems and procedures using graphical and video development tools as well as proprietary simulation based editors.</p>
<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul><li>Work as a member of a highly-creative, highly-collaborative and fast-paced e-learning design and development team</li>
<li>Design and implement computer based training (CBT) for pilots, maintenance technicians and cabin crew in the general, commercial and military aviation industries</li>
<li>Develop and execute project plans to ensure timely delivery of learning modules</li>
</ul><p><strong>Training will be provided for:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Proprietary Lesson Plan Editing tools to develop simulation based courseware</li>
<li>Adobe Graphics Suite, including Photoshop and Illustrator, for the development of graphical components</li>
<li>Adobe Flash, including basic Action Script to integrate the graphical, animation, audio, and simulation components into comprehensive interactive scenario based courseware</li>
</ul><p><strong>Education and Experience</strong></p>
<p><strong>Required:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Private Pilot License</li>
<li>1-4+ years’ experience in an aviation related environment</li>
<li><span style="font-family:inherit; font-size:1.0625rem; line-height:1.4">Understand basic principles of aircraft systems and procedures (Hydraulics, Electrical, Navigation, FMS, CRM etc.)</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:inherit; font-size:1.0625rem; line-height:1.4">Proficiency in the use of Microsoft Office and Adobe Graphics Suites</span></li>
</ul><p><strong>Preferred:</strong>​</p>
<ul><li>Experience in graphic development using the Adobe Graphics Suite (including Photoshop, Illustrator and Flash) for use in interactive training programs</li>
<li>Proficiency in development of interactive multimedia online instruction</li>
</ul><p><strong>For consideration, please submit cover letter and resume.</strong></p>
